---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About SQLTemple"
  description="What SQLTemple is, why it exists, and the stack behind it."
>
  <section class="container section space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">About SQLTemple</h1>
    <p class="text-muted text-lg max-w-3xl">
      SQLTemple is an AI-powered SQL IDE built by Victor Bona. It blends the
      Monaco editor with execution plan insights and OpenAI assistance so you
      can ship faster SQL safely.
    </p>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface-2 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Tech stack</h3>
        <ul class="text-muted space-y-2">
          <li>Electron + React + TypeScript</li>
          <li>Monaco Editor for the editing core</li>
          <li>OpenAI models (GPT-4o, o1) for explanations & optimization</li>
          <li>PostgreSQL support first, more engines next</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface-2 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Why build it?</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Traditional SQL tools are either heavy or lack modern AI assistance.
          SQLTemple keeps the workflow lean, dark-themed, and tuned for
          iteration speed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
